# Nagios monitoring for manual inventory

- Keep structured facts in the matching `*.json` sidecar next to the `.md` file. For hosts that should appear in Nagios, define `access.nodes` entries with `ip`, optional `name`, `web_ui` (for HTTPS/HTTP checks), and `ssh` (e.g. `ssh://root@10.0.0.1`) so SSH-based deploy can resolve users without guessing.
- Add `"nagios"` to `automation_targets` when this resource is monitored or touched by the Nagios package so `node tools/hdc/cli.mjs docs lint` stays consistent with manifests under `packages/nagios/`.
- After inventory edits, run `node tools/hdc/cli.mjs docs lint` (optional `docs sync` runs the same JSON validation; hdc does not modify companion `.md` files).
- When checks or hosts change, redeploy: `node tools/hdc/cli.mjs run nagios deploy` (requires `nagios.central` on [`inventory/manual/systems/pve-a.json`](inventory/manual/systems/pve-a.json) and NRPE **TCP 5666** allowed from the central Nagios host to each Proxmox node).
